The paper discusses Constraint Logic Programming (CLP) and Concurrent Constraint Programming (CCP), which are both subfields of Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper also focuses on dynamic slicing, which is a technique used in software engineering (cs.SE) to identify and remove irrelevant information from a program. Additionally, the paper mentions an assertion language, which is a tool used in formal verification (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to specify properties of a program. Finally, the paper uses experiments to demonstrate the usefulness of the approach, which falls under Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
